SIMPLE: dimorphous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dimorphous
<hw>Di*mor"phous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>dimorphe</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Characterized by dimorphism; occurring under two distinct forms,
not dependent on sex; dimorphic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Crystallizing under two
forms fundamentally different, while having the same chemical
composition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dimple</ent>⟦br⟧
